news.title: Colonies handed over to Gurugram civic body in June, but infrastructure still deficient: RWA
news.para: They alleged that the issues have only gotten worse in the last few weeks, with the civic authority having done little to resolve the issues since it took charge of the colony.

news.title: Gurugram: No ban on sale deeds by homeowners in Sushant Lok-2, says DTCP
news.para: On Tuesday, senior town planner Narendra Solanki said the DTCP order was applicable on properties owned by the developer, and not the residents.

news.title: Asian Paints' profit jumps 80.4% to Rs 1,036 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 55 per cent to Rs 8,578.88 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 5,534.87 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Axis Mutual Fund to launch Rs 1,500 crore fund for developing realty projects
news.para: The partnership will invest in early-stage or greenfield commercial real estate projects across the Mumbai region, Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Chennai, Pune, Ahmedabad and Kolkata, Axis AMC said in a statement on Tuesday.

news.title: SC grants bail to director of Pune-based DSK Group in fraud case
news.para: ​​A bench of justices S A Nazeer and J K Maheshwari allowed the appeal of Kulkarni against the August 17, 2021 order of the Bombay High Court rejecting his bail plea in the case.

news.title: ED allowed to take ex-director of Guru Ashish Construction to Delhi in PACL case
news.para: He was arrested by the ED in February this year in a money laundering probe linked to a Rs 1,034-crore land scam related to the redevelopment of a chawl in Mumbai.

news.title: Realtors against state government on registry issue in Punjab
news.para: The sector’s biggest demand is that the colonies existing till 2022 be regularised without NOC and the receipt be issued on the spot for quick registry.

news.title: Edelweiss Securities leases 1 lakh sq ft in Adani Realty's office tower in Mumbai
news.para: The firm is expected to pay total rentals worth over Rs 285 crore over the tenure of the lease based on monthly rentals of Rs 220 per sq ft, including common area maintenance charges.

news.title: Punjab to use GPS tracking, bar code scanners to check illegal sand mining: Report
news.para: The recommendations include use of digital technology such as remote sensing data in order to scientifically determine the extent of legal and illegal sand mining in and around the operational sand mining sites in the state.

news.title: Chandigarh: Extra FAR charges likely to be based on type of properties
news.para: The UT administration is going to adopt different formula for calculating charges for different types of properties in connection with availing additional floor area ratio (FAR). In the coming days, the UT will also form a sub-committee in this regard.

news.title: Not a single taker for 25 freehold properties of Chandigarh housing board
news.para: The board had invited bids for the sale of 25 built-up properties, including 23 residential and two commercial, on freehold basis.

news.title: Rajasthan: Prashasan campaign picks up pace, more pattas being issued
news.para: At the Jaipur Development Authority, which is considered as biggest civic body in the state, the administration has issued 5,500 Pattas in last 10 days.

news.title: Chandigarh: 50% property tax waiver for EWS houses
news.para: Approval was also given to waive off 100% penalty amount of three financial years of 2019-2020, 2020-2021 and 2021-2022 of the EWS houses.

news.title: Raze illegal buildings obstructing flights where there's no stay: Bombay HC
news.para: Mumbai International Airport Ltd had in its July 8 reply given details of obstacle surveys carried out by it over the years.

news.title: Gurugram: Two years on, AVL 36 residents yet to get an elected RWA
news.para: The residents have complained that the developer had registered an apartment owners association in March 2020 and nominated its close aides as the office bearers of the association without holding any election process.
